  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CONSTRUCTION PROJECT MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Construction Project Manager is responsible for leading construction projects to successful completion by delivering on time, within budget, and meeting quality standards. You will plan, coordinate, and supervise (<strong>M&E Field ; PLUMBING AND SANITARY WORKS ; FIRE PROTECTION ;  ACMV!)</strong> and related activities while engaging effectively with clients, architects, engineers, and contractors.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Develop and implement detailed project plans with clear goals, objectives, and timelines to drive project success</strong></li><li><strong>Prepare and submit comprehensive project plans / reports \"covering progress, costs, materials & manpower\"</strong></li><li>Establish and control project budgets to minimize expenses and optimize resource allocation</li><li>Oversee on-site construction activities to ensure adherence to safety regulations, building codes, and quality standards</li><li>Manage contractors and subcontractors by selecting, evaluating, and monitoring their performance to maintain project standards</li><li>Coordinate communication among clients, architects, engineers, and contractors to align project expectations and progress</li><li>Identify potential risks including safety hazards, schedule delays, and cost overruns, and implement mitigation strategies</li><li>Enforce quality control processes to detect and rectify defects, ensuring construction work meets required standards</li><li>Develop and maintain project schedules to meet milestones and deadlines consistently</li><li>Ensure construction site safety by enforcing compliance with safety regulations and best practices</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Diploma qualification as a minimum educational requirement</strong></li><li><strong>Minimum 5 years of experience in a similar role within the M&E -> Plumbing & Sanitary, Fire Protection & ACMV industries</strong></li><li><strong>Proficient in using AutoCAD for project planning and design coordination</strong></li><li><strong>Proficient in using Microsoft Office </strong></li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge, Familiarity & Expertise in Mechanical & Electrical (M&E) -> Plumbing and Sanitary works ;  Fire Protection & ACMV systems</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
